parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The timing chain makes a loud noise
the engine stalls or fails to start
the vehicle loses power
the engine has excessive play
the timing chain has broken pieces
the engine has bent valves
the vehicle has no compression.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine has no compression
the engine stalls or fails to start
the vehicle loses power
the engine has excessive noise
the engine has bent valves
the vehicle has a sulfur-like smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to safety issues.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the ignition switch fails to turn
the vehicle won't start
and accessories may be defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause various components to fail, leading to safety issues, such as brake light failure, and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The brake lights
turn signals
and other electrical components fail to function
the security light flashes
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to safety issues.
symptoms: The security light flashes
the vehicle won't start
and the key may not turn in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can lead to accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop, which can result in rear-ending or other collisions.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate or intermittently fail to work when the headlights are turned on
and the bulb is good.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal can lead to accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to turn or change lanes.
symptoms: The turn signal does not activate or deactivates
and the hazard warning switch assembly may make a loud buzzing sound
especially in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can lead to accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop or turn, and the vehicle may not be visible in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights
taillights
or brake lights may not work or work intermittently
and there may be smoke coming from the steering column or other electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Design Flaw in Tail Light Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the tail light assembly can lead to accidents, as the brake lights may not work or work intermittently, and the vehicle may not be visible in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate or intermittently fail to work when the headlights are turned on
and the bulb is good.
